cs.PL, cs.LO, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.FL 

This paper deals with logic programming and program analysis, which are both subfields of programming languages (cs.PL) and theoretical computer science (cs.LO). The paper also mentions declarative debugging, which is a technique used in software engineering (cs.SE). The use of abstract interpretation to analyze properties of the program suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper specifically deals with floundering, which is a concept related to coroutining and control flow in logic programming, making the sub-category of formal languages and automata theory (cs.FL) a possible fit as well.
